OL,3,CThe kayakers paddling for plastic in
OL,4,Chard to reach places
OL,6,FNone of this plastic will biodegrade.
OL,7,FInstead it will break up into smaller
OL,8,Fand smaller pieces.
OL,10,FThese microplastics then make their
OL,11,Fway into our ecosystem - and even our
OL,12,Ffood chain - when they are eaten by
OL,13,Fbirds, fish and other wildlife.
OL,15,FBut one organisation, Odyssey
OL,16,FInnovation, is trying to change that.
OL,17,FThe firm takes plastic collected at
OL,18,Fbeach cleans or gathered by community
OL,19,Fgroups, as well as waste from harbours
OL,20,Fand recycles it.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/8
