OL,3,CThe kayakers paddling for plastic in
OL,4,Chard to reach places
OL,6,F"It kind of becomes a bit of a
OL,7,Ftreasure hunt. Not necessarily a good
OL,8,Ftreasure hunt," she added. "But at
OL,9,Fleast you know it's being removed and
OL,10,Fhopefully repurposed, or at least
OL,11,Fremoved from the shoreline."
OL,13,FIt is easy for the group to pick up
OL,14,Fthe larger items that wash up, but
OL,15,Fmicroplastics prove trickier to clear.
OL,17,FPicking up a handful of driftwood,
OL,18,FGary Jolliffe told ITV News: "In
OL,19,Famongst all this natural material,
OL,20,Fthere are thousands of pieces of
OL,21,Fmicroplastic.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/8
