OL,3,CThe kayakers paddling for plastic in
OL,4,Chard to reach places
OL,6,F"You've got nurdles - the base of all
OL,7,Fmoulded plastics. That's how they get
OL,8,Ftransported, the little circular
OL,9,Fnurdles.
OL,11,F"There are literally hundreds of
OL,12,Fparticles of plastics mixed in amongst
OL,13,Fthis natural material - and as you dig
OL,14,Fdown you start finding more of it.
OL,15,FThis is what it's like on every
OL,16,Fstretch of the coastline all around
OL,17,Fthe UK and dare I say all around the
OL,18,Fglobe."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/8
